nodes.name: withdrawFromStore

approveStore(bool,uint16).details: Allows marketpalce owner to approve store proposals.

params._indexInStoresArray: The index at which to put the new store in the store proposal owner's stores array if approved.
params._isApproved: Specifies whether the current store proposal is approved.

getStoreOwners().details: Allows returning all current store owners.
getStoreOwners().return: Array of addresses of store owners.

getStoresByOwner(address).details: Allows returning the according stores to the specified address.

params._owner: The address of which stores to get.

init().details: Initializes the msg sender as an owner account.

isStoreOwner(address).details: Allows verifying whether the specified address is a store owner.
isStoreOwner(address).return: Boolean variable specifying whether the address is owner's or not.

ownerWithdraw(address,uint256).details: Allows the current owner to withdraw funds from the marketplace.

params._amount: The amount of the funds transferred.
params._recipient: The address to transfer the funds to.

requestStore(bytes32).details: Allows users to request a store.

params._proposal: Hexadecimal representation of an IPFS hash of file or folder holding the proposal materials.

revokeStore(address,uint16).details: Allows the marketplace to delete store and call it's `destruct` function.

params._storeIndex: The store index in the store owner's stores array.
params._storeOwner: The store owner of whom to revoke store.

transferOwnership(address).details: Allows the current owner to transfer control of the contract to a new owner.

params._newOwner: The address to transfer ownership to.

transferStoreOwnership(address,uint16,ad.details: Provides with transferring store ownership functionality.

params._newOwnerStoreIndex: The index at which to put the new store in the new store owner's stores array.
params._storeIndex: The current store index in the store owner's stores array.

upgradeImplementation(address).details: Allows current owner to upgrade the implementation to which the `Forwardable` contract delegates calls.

withdrawFromStore(address,uint256).details: Allows the marketplace to withdraw funds from stores back to the marketplace.

params._amount: The amount of the funds to be withdrawed.
params._storeAddress: The address of the store from which to withdraw.

approveStore(bool,uint16).notice: The store requests are processed in FIFO manner.

requestStore(bytes32).notice: The proposal argument is a processed hexadecimal representation of the default IPFS SHA-256 hash with removed prefix.

transferStoreOwnership(address,uint16,ad.notice: Allows the owners to specify an empty index at which to push the new store in order to fill the deleted stores blank spaces
